OL,6,F"We acknowledge too, that the idea of
OL,7,Fevidence being heard in circumstances
OL,8,Fin which the families and survivors
OL,9,Fwill be excluded is one that they will
OL,10,Ffind difficult to accept, to say the
OL,11,Fleast, and accordingly, we regard it
OL,12,Fas entirely understandable that some,
OL,13,Falthough not all, have suggested
OL,14,Fspecial advocates should be appointed
OL,15,Fto represent their interests in any
OL,16,Fclosed hearings, and have made
OL,17,Fapplications for that to occur," he
OL,18,Fsaid.
